56 (F) One individual who represents a nonprofit entity with knowledge relative to
57 Georgia pollution impacts; and
58 (G) One community member who sits at the intersection of pollution and economic
59 development.
60 The Speaker shall designate a legislative member of the committee as chairperson of the
61 committee.
62 (3) Powers and duties. The committee shall undertake a study of the conditions, needs,
63 issues, and problems mentioned above or related thereto and recommend any action or
64 legislation which the committee deems necessary or appropriate.
65 (4) Meetings. The chairperson shall call all meetings of the committee. The committee
66 may conduct such meetings at such places and at such times as it may deem necessary or
67 convenient to enable it to exercise fully and effectively its powers, perform its duties, and
68 accomplish the objectives and purposes of this resolution.
69 (5) Allowances, expenses, and funding.
70 (A) The legislative members of the committee shall receive the allowances provided
71 for in Code Section 28-1-8 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated.
72 (B) Members of the committee who are state officials, other than legislative members,
73 or who are state employees shall receive no compensation for their services on the
74 committee, but they may be reimbursed for expenses incurred by them in the
75 performance of their duties as members of the committee in the same manner as they
76 are reimbursed for expenses in their capacities as state officials or employees.
77 (C) Members of the committee who are not legislators, state officials, or state
78 employees shall receive a daily expense allowance in an amount the same as that
79 specified in subsection (b) of Code Section 45-7-21 of the Official Code of Georgia
80 Annotated, as well as the mileage or transportation allowance authorized for state
81 employees.
