82 (D) The allowances authorized by this resolution shall not be received by any member
83 of the committee for more than five days unless additional days are authorized. Funds
84 necessary to carry out the provisions of this resolution shall come from funds
85 appropriated to the House of Representatives; except that funds for the reimbursement
86 of the expenses of state officials, other than legislative members, and for the
87 reimbursement of the expenses of state employees shall come from funds appropriated
88 to or otherwise available to their respective agencies.
89 (6) Report.
90 (A) In the event the committee adopts any specific findings or recommendations that
91 include suggestions for proposed legislation, the chairperson shall file a report of the
92 same prior to the date of abolishment specified in this resolution, subject to
93 subparagraph (C) of this paragraph.
94 (B) In the event the committee adopts a report that does not include suggestions for
95 proposed legislation, the chairperson shall file the report, subject to subparagraph (C)
96 of this paragraph.
97 (C) No report shall be filed unless the same has been approved prior to the date of
98 abolishment specified in this resolution by majority vote of a quorum of the committee.
99 A report so approved shall be signed by the chairperson of the committee and filed with
100 the Clerk of the House of Representatives.
101 (D) In the absence of an approved report, the chairperson may file with the Clerk of the
102 House of Representatives a copy of the minutes of the meetings of the committee in lieu
103 thereof.
104 (7) Abolishment. The committee shall stand abolished on December 1, 2025.
